'''Jhon Adolfo Arias Andrade''' (born 21 September 1997) is a Colombian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as [[wide midfielder]] or [[attacking midfielder]] for [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[SE Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] and the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]].

After beginning his career in Colombia with [[Patriotas Boyacá|Patriotas]], he moved to [[América de Cali]], where he won the [[Categoría Primera A]] in [[2020 Categoría Primera A season|2020]]. He later joined [[Independiente Santa Fe|Santa Fe]] before transferring to Brazil with [[Fluminense FC|Fluminense]]. In [[2022 Campeonato Carioca|2022]], he won the Campeonato Carioca, and in [[2023 Campeonato Carioca|2023]] he added another Campeonato Carioca and the [[2023 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores]], while being named to the [[2023 Campeonato Carioca|Campeonato Carioca Team of the Year]], the [[2023 Copa Libertadores|Copa Libertadores Team of the Tournament]], the [[2023 Campeonato Brasileiro Série A|Campeonato Brasileiro Série A Team of the Year]], and the South American Team of the Year. In [[2024 Recopa Sudamericana|2024]], he won the Recopa Sudamericana, and in [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup|2025]] he was named to the FIFA Club World Cup Team of the Tournament. Later that year, he transferred to [[Wolverhampton Wanderers]], signing a four-year contract with an option for an additional year.

Arias made his senior international debut for Colombia in 2022, and was part of the squad that finished runners-up at the [[2024 Copa América]].

==Club career==
===Early career===
Born in [[Quibdó]], Arias represented Mexican sides [[Dorados de Sinaloa]] and [[Club Tijuana|Tijuana]] as a youth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.noroeste.com.mx/deportes/futbol/jhon-arias-el-crack-del-fluminense-que-estuvo-en-las-fuerzas-basicas-de-dorados-ED13891995|title=Jhon Arias, el crack del Fluminense que estuvo en las fuerzas básicas de Dorados|trans-title=Jhon Arias, the baller of Fluminense who was in the youth sides of Dorados|publisher=Noroeste|language=es|date=22 June 2025|accessdate=15 July 2025}}</ref> He returned to his home country in 2017 and signed for [[Patriotas Boyacá]], before moving out on loan to [[Llaneros F.C.|Llaneros]] for the 2018 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://dimayor.com.co/2021/04/talento-jhon-arias/|title=TALENTO: JHON ARIAS|trans-title=TALENT: JHON ARIAS|publisher=Dimayor|language=es|date=15 April 2021|access-date=9 November 2021}}</ref>

After making his senior debut with Llaneros in the 2018 [[Categoría Primera B]], Arias returned to Patriotas for the [[2019 Categoría Primera A season|2019 Categoría Primera A]]. Regularly used, he scored four goals in 38 appearances overall.

===América de Cali===
On 10 December 2019, Arias signed a contract with [[América de Cali]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elpais.com.co/america-de-cali/eder-chaux-primer-refuerzo-escarlata-confirmado-para-el-la-temporada-2020.html|title=Eder Chaux y Jhon Arias, los primeros refuerzos de América de Cali para el 2020|trans-title=Eder Chaux and Jhon Arias, the first two additions of América de Cali for 2020|publisher=[[El País (Cali)|El País]]|language=es|date=10 December 2019|access-date=9 November 2021}}</ref> He was unable to establish himself as a regular starter, scoring once in 29 matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elespectador.com/deportes/futbol-colombiano/santa-fe/la-escalera-al-cielo-de-jhon-arias-article/|title=La escalera al cielo de Jhon Arias|trans-title=Jhon Arias' stairway to heaven|publisher=[[El Espectador]]|language=es|date=17 February 2021|accessdate=15 July 2025}}</ref>

===Independiente Santa Fe===
On 7 January 2021, Arias joined [[Independiente Santa Fe]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://colombia.as.com/colombia/2021/01/07/futbol/1610031877_881253.html|title=Santa Fe hace oficial la llegada de Jhon Arias como refuerzo|trans-title=Santa Fe turn official the arrival of Jhon Arias as an addition|publisher=[[Diario AS]]|language=es|date=7 January 2021|access-date=9 November 2021}}</ref> He quickly became a first-choice at his new side, and despite finishing winless in the group stage of [[2021 Copa Libertadores]], his performances attracted the interest of foreign clubs.

===Fluminense===
On 18 August 2021, Arias moved abroad for the first time in his career, after agreeing to a four-year contract with [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] side [[Fluminense FC|Fluminense]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fluminense.com.br/noticia/fluminense-assina-com-jhon-arias-ate-2025|title=Fluminense assina com Jhon Arias até 2025|trans-title=Fluminense sign with Jhon Arias until 2025|publisher=Fluminense FC|language=pt-BR|date=18 August 2021|access-date=9 November 2021}}</ref> He made his debut abroad twelve days later, starting in a 2–0 home win over [[Esporte Clube Bahia|Bahia]], and scored his first goal on 2 September, in a 1–1 home draw against [[Esporte Clube Juventude|Juventude]].

After a first season mainly a backup, Arias subsequently became a starter, and was a part of the squad that won the club's first ever [[Copa Libertadores]] in [[2023 Copa Libertadores|2023]], by beating [[Boca Juniors]] 2–1 in the final.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tntsports.com.br/futebolbrasileiro/Fluminense-vence-o-Boca-Juniors-e-e-campeao-da-Libertadores-pela-primeira-vez-20231104-0016.html|title=Fluminense vence o Boca Juniors e é campeão da Libertadores pela primeira vez|trans-title=Fluminense defeat Boca Juniors and are Libertadores champions for the first time|publisher=TNT Sports BR|language=pt-BR|date=4 November 2023|access-date=18 May 2024}}</ref> He was also nominated for the [[South American Footballer of the Year]] in that year, but finished fourth.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.terra.com.br/esportes/fluminense/indicado-ao-premio-de-rei-da-america-jhon-arias-foi-o-garcom-do-fluminense-em-2023,2514d75b7199e49c8155dad7c43eb68e8hyvmm5s.html|title=Indicado ao prêmio de Rei da América, Jhon Arias foi o garçom do Fluminense em 2023|trans-title=Nominated to the Rey de América, Jhon Arias was the assist leader of Fluminense in 2003|publisher=[[Terra (company)|terra]]|language=pt-BR|date=28 December 2023|accessdate=15 July 2025}}</ref>

Arias' performances at the [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup]] earned him a nomination to the team of the tournament, having scored one goal, provided one assist and helped his side reach the semi-finals. His final appearance for Fluminense came in the team's first match following the World Cup, a 2–0 loss to Cruzeiro at the [[Maracanã Stadium|Maracanã]].<ref>{{Cite journal |last=Hoffmann |first=Andre |last2=Lobão |first2=Adriana |last3=Joffily |first3=Ana |last4=Brandes |first4=Arno |last5=Boscolo |first5=Odara |last6=Paiva |first6=Selma |date=2024-12-30 |title=Plantas medicinais |url=https://doi.org/10.24927/rce2024.036 |journal=Revista de Ciência Elementar |volume=12 |issue=4 |doi=10.24927/rce2024.036 |issn=2183-1270|doi-access=free }}</ref>

===Wolverhampton Wanderers===
[[File:Jhon Arias 01112025 (2).jpg|thumb|left|150px|Arias warming up before a match for [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in 2025]]
On 18 July 2025, Fluminense announced an agreement for the transfer of Arias to [[Premier League]] club [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/article/fluminense-confirm-sale-jhon-arias-205200959.html|title=Fluminense confirm sale of Jhon Arias to Wolves|publisher=Yahoo Sports|date=18 July 2025|accessdate=19 July 2025}}</ref> The deal was completed on 24 July on a four-year contract with the option of an additional year's extension.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wolves.co.uk/news/mens-first-team/20250724-arias-makes-molineux-move/|title=Arias makes Molineux move|publisher=Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|date=24 July 2025|accessdate=24 July 2025}}</ref>

===Palmeiras===
On 7 February 2026, Arias returned to Brazil, this time joining [[SE Palmeiras|Palmeiras]] on a three-year contract for €25 million paid over four years in [[instalments]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/fr/news/palmeiras-sign-jhon-arias-from-wolverhampton-on-contract-to-2029-42373531|work=OneFootball|title=Palmeiras sign Jhon Arias from Wolverhampton on contract to 2029|date=February 7, 2026|access-date=February 7, 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
[[File:Jhon Arias (2024).jpg|thumb|right|180px|Arias with the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]] in 2024]]
On 24 May 2022, Arias was called up to the [[Colombia national football team|Colombia national team]] for a friendly against [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fluminense.com.br/noticia/jhon-arias-e-convocado-para-defender-a-selecao-da-colombia|title=Jhon Arias é convocado para defender a seleção da Colômbia|trans-title=Jhon Arias is called up to play for the Colombia national team|publisher=Fluminense FC|language=pt-BR|date=24 May 2022|accessdate=15 July 2025}}</ref> He made his full international debut on 5 June, starting in the 1–0 win at the [[Estadio Nueva Condomina]] in [[Murcia]], Spain.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.infobae.com/america/agencias/2022/06/05/una-renovada-colombia-derrota-1-0-a-la-mundialista-arabia-saudita-en-amistoso/|title=Una renovada Colombia derrota 1–0 a la mundialista Arabia Saudita en amistoso|trans-title=A renewed Colombia defeat World Cup's Saudi Arabia 1–0 in a friendly|publisher=[[Infobae]]|language=es|date=5 June 2022|accessdate=15 July 2025}}</ref>

Arias scored his first goal for Colombia on 26 March 2024, scoring his side's second in a 3–2 win over [[Romania national football team|Romania]] at the [[Metropolitano Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://caracol.com.co/2024/03/26/asi-fue-el-gol-de-jhon-arias-en-el-amistoso-entre-colombia-rumania/|title=Así fue el gol de Jhon Arias en el Amistoso entre Colombia – Rumania|trans-title=This was the goal of Jhon Arias in the friendly against Colombia – Romania|publisher=[[Caracol Radio]]|language=es|date=26 March 2024|accessdate=15 July 2025}}</ref> On 23 May, he was included in the squad for the [[2024 Copa América]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fluminense.com.br/noticia/jhon-arias-e-convocado-para-defender-a-colombia-na-copa-america|title=Jhon Arias é convocado para defender a Colômbia na Copa América|trans-title=Jhon Arias is called up to play for Colombia in the Copa América|publisher=Fluminense FC|language=pt-BR|date=23 May 2024|accessdate=15 July 2025}}</ref>

